---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Professional profile of Miguel Ramirez Exojo — senior cloud infrastructure contractor working remotely across Europe."
>
  <section class="page-head section">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Senior cloud and DevSecOps engineer, contracting remotely across Europe.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      I design, automate, and operate cloud platforms as an independent B2B contractor,
      in engagements scoped to a clear outcome and handed over to the team that keeps them.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section prose-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Summary</p>
      <h2>Over 19 years in systems, cloud and infrastructure.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-stack">
      <p>
        I'm Miguel Ramirez Exojo — 19 years in IT, the last eight focused on cloud
        architecture, Infrastructure as Code, FinOps, and DevSecOps across AWS, GCP,
        and Azure. Freelance since 2022, with client engagements including Orange Bank,
        SantaLucía, and Jefferson Frank IT Consulting; before that, cloud infrastructure
        roles at Copado (US), Sngular (Decathlon, Telefónica Foundation), and Nokia.
      </p>
      <p>
        Typical stack: Terraform, Kubernetes (EKS, GKE, AKS), GitHub Actions, Ansible,
        Python. Certifications include AWS Solutions Architect and Security Specialty,
        Google Cloud Engineer, HashiCorp Terraform Associate, FinOps Certified
        Practitioner, and Linux LPIC-3. I work with engineering teams across Europe —
        DACH, the Netherlands, the UK, Benelux, and the Nordics — from Spain (CET).
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-label="Experience summary">
    <div class="about-ledger">
      <article>
        <span>01</span>
        <h3>Current focus</h3>
        <p>Cloud architecture and migration, Infrastructure as Code, FinOps cost optimization, and DevSecOps delivery pipelines.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>02</span>
        <h3>Technologies</h3>
        <p>Terraform, Ansible, Kubernetes, Docker, Linux, AWS, GCP, Azure and OpenStack.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>03</span>
        <h3>Collaboration</h3>
        <p>Remote B2B engagements across Europe — CET working hours, EU VAT registered, fixed scope or retainer.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section prose-grid about-closing">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Method</p>
      <h2>Solve first, complicate less.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-stack">
      <p>
        I focus on making infrastructure useful for business and easy to operate:
        clear decisions, repeatable deployments, understandable costs and real recovery
        capability when something fails.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
